Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
write_net_groups_topo(25.10)                      write_net_groups_topo(25.10)

Name
       write_net_groups_topo  -  Creates  a  topological file (used by the in-
       sertPtnFeedthrough command) for nets of the net group associated with a
       bus guide

Syntax
       write_net_groups_topo

       [-help]

       [-net_groups <list_of_net_groups>]

       [-outFile <file_name>]

       Creates a topological file (used by the  insertPtnFeedthrough  command)
       for  nets of the net group associated with a bus guide. The topology of
       nets for feedthrough is derived from the shape of the  bus  guide.  All
       the partitions that the bus guide shape overlaps with, become a node in
       the topological path.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each write_net_groups_topo parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man write_net_groups_topo

       -net_groups <list_of_net_groups>
              Specifies the net groups to be added in topo file.

              Default: *.

              For example, the following command specifies that the ng1,  ng2,
              and ng3 netgroups must be added to the topo file.

              write_net_groups_topo -net_groups {ng1 ng2 ng3-*}

              Data_type: string, optional

       -outFile <file_name>
              Writes the bus guide violation log to the specified file.

              Default: bus_guided.topo.v2

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
              * The  following  command  writes the net group information to a
                topology file.

                write_net_groups_topo

Related Information
              * Partitioning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

